name: storage
title: Cloud Storage JSON API
description: Lets you store and retrieve potentially-large, immutable data objects.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

schemas.name: Channel
schemas.desc: An notification channel used to watch for resource changes.

fields.name: address
fields.desc: The address where notifications are delivered for this channel.

fields.name: token
fields.desc: An arbitrary string delivered to the target address with each notification delivered over this channel. Optional.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies this as a notification channel used to watch for changes to a resource. Value: the fixed string "api#channel".

fields.name: params
fields.desc: Additional parameters controlling delivery channel behavior. Optional.

fields.name: payload
fields.desc: A Boolean value to indicate whether payload is wanted. Optional.

fields.name: resourceId
fields.desc: An opaque ID that identifies the resource being watched on this channel. Stable across different API versions.

fields.name: resourceUri
fields.desc: A version-specific identifier for the watched resource.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The type of delivery mechanism used for this channel.

fields.name: expiration
fields.desc: Date and time of notification channel expiration, expressed as a Unix timestamp, in milliseconds. Optional.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: A UUID or similar unique string that identifies this channel.

fields.name: destination
fields.desc: Properties of the resulting object

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is.

fields.name: sourceObjects
fields.desc: The list of source objects that will be concatenated into a single object.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The source object's name. The source object's bucket is implicitly the destination bucket.

fields.name: objectPreconditions
fields.desc: Conditions that must be met for this operation to execute.

fields.name: ifGenerationMatch
fields.desc: Only perform the composition if the generation of the source object that would be used matches this value. If this value and a generation are both specified, they must be the same value or the call will fail.

fields.name: generation
fields.desc: The generation of this object to use as the source.

fields.name: updated
fields.desc: Modification time of the object metadata in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: cacheControl
fields.desc: Cache-Control directive for the object data.

fields.name: generation
fields.desc: The content generation of this object. Used for object versioning.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For objects, this is always storage#object.

fields.name: metadata
fields.desc: User-provided metadata, in key/value pairs.

fields.name: owner
fields.desc: The owner of the object. This will always be the uploader of the object.

fields.name: entity
fields.desc: The entity, in the form user-userId.

fields.name: entityId
fields.desc: The ID for the entity.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the object.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The link to this object.

fields.name: size
fields.desc: Content-Length of the data in bytes.

fields.name: acl
fields.desc: Access controls on the object.

fields.name: contentDisposition
fields.desc: Content-Disposition of the object data.

fields.name: contentLanguage
fields.desc: Content-Language of the object data.

fields.name: contentType
fields.desc: Content-Type of the object data.

fields.name: crc32c
fields.desc: CRC32c checksum, as described in RFC 4960, Appendix B; encoded using base64.

fields.name: storageClass
fields.desc: Storage class of the object.

fields.name: bucket
fields.desc: The bucket containing this object.

fields.name: md5Hash
fields.desc: MD5 hash of the data; encoded using base64.

fields.name: mediaLink
fields.desc: Media download link.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of this object. Required if not specified by URL parameter.

fields.name: componentCount
fields.desc: Number of underlying components that make up this object. Components are accumulated by compose operations and are limited to a count of 32.

fields.name: contentEncoding
fields.desc: Content-Encoding of the object data.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the object.

fields.name: metageneration
fields.desc: The generation of the metadata for this object at this generation. Used for metadata versioning. Has no meaning outside of the context of this generation.

fields.name: timeDeleted
fields.desc: Deletion time of the object in RFC 3339 format. Will be returned if and only if this version of the object has been deleted.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of items.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For lists of object access control entries, this is always storage#objectAccessControls.

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: The continuation token, used to page through large result sets. Provide this value in a subsequent request to return the next page of results.

fields.name: prefixes
fields.desc: The list of prefixes of objects matching-but-not-listed up to and including the requested delimiter.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: The list of items.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For lists of objects, this is always storage#objects.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For buckets, this is always storage#bucket.

fields.name: lifecycle
fields.desc: The bucket's lifecycle configuration. See object lifecycle management for more information.

fields.name: rule
fields.desc: A lifecycle management rule, which is made of an action to take and the condition(s) under which the action will be taken.

fields.name: action
fields.desc: The action to take.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: Type of the action. Currently only Delete is supported.

fields.name: condition
fields.desc: The condition(s) under which the action will be taken.

fields.name: createdBefore
fields.desc: A date in RFC 3339 format with only the date part, e.g. "2013-01-15". This condition is satisfied when an object is created before midnight of the specified date in UTC.

fields.name: isLive
fields.desc: Relevant only for versioned objects. If the value is true, this condition matches live objects; if the value is false, it matches archived objects.

fields.name: numNewerVersions
fields.desc: Relevant only for versioned objects. If the value is N, this condition is satisfied when there are at least N versions (including the live version) newer than this version of the object.

fields.name: age
fields.desc: Age of an object (in days). This condition is satisfied when an object reaches the specified age.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: The location of the bucket. Object data for objects in the bucket resides in physical storage within this region. Typical values are US and EU. Defaults to US. See the developer's guide for the authoritative list.

fields.name: owner
fields.desc: The owner of the bucket. This is always the project team's owner group.

fields.name: entity
fields.desc: The entity, in the form group-groupId.

fields.name: entityId
fields.desc: The ID for the entity.

fields.name: versioning
fields.desc: The bucket's versioning configuration.

fields.name: enabled
fields.desc: While set to true, versioning is fully enabled for this bucket.

fields.name: website
fields.desc: The bucket's website configuration.

fields.name: mainPageSuffix
fields.desc: Behaves as the bucket's directory index where missing objects are treated as potential directories.

fields.name: notFoundPage
fields.desc: The custom object to return when a requested resource is not found.

fields.name: defaultObjectAcl
fields.desc: Default access controls to apply to new objects when no ACL is provided.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the bucket.

fields.name: selfLink
fields.desc: The URI of this bucket.

fields.name: storageClass
fields.desc: The bucket's storage class. This defines how objects in the bucket are stored and determines the SLA and the cost of storage. Typical values are STANDARD and DURABLE_REDUCED_AVAILABILITY. Defaults to STANDARD. See the developer's guide for the authoritative list.

fields.name: timeCreated
fields.desc: Creation time of the bucket in RFC 3339 format.

fields.name: acl
fields.desc: Access controls on the bucket.

fields.name: cors
fields.desc: The bucket's Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) configuration.

fields.name: method
fields.desc: The list of HTTP methods on which to include CORS response headers: GET, OPTIONS, POST, etc. Note, "*" is permitted in the list of methods, and means "any method".

fields.name: origin
fields.desc: The list of Origins eligible to receive CORS response headers. Note: "*" is permitted in the list of origins, and means "any Origin".

fields.name: responseHeader
fields.desc: The list of HTTP headers other than the simple response headers to give permission for the user-agent to share across domains.

fields.name: maxAgeSeconds
fields.desc: The value, in seconds, to return in the  Access-Control-Max-Age header used in preflight responses.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: HTTP 1.1 Entity tag for the bucket.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the bucket.

fields.name: logging
fields.desc: The bucket's logging configuration, which defines the destination bucket and optional name prefix for the current bucket's logs.

fields.name: logBucket
fields.desc: The destination bucket where the current bucket's logs should be placed.

fields.name: logObjectPrefix
fields.desc: A prefix for log object names.

fields.name: metageneration
fields.desc: The metadata generation of this bucket.

fields.name: entity
fields.desc:
The entity holding the permission, in one of the following forms: 
- user-userId 
- user-email 
- group-groupId 
- group-email 
- domain-domain 
- allUsers 
- allAuthenticatedUsers Examples: 
- The user liz@example.com would be user-liz@example.com. 
- The group example@googlegroups.com would be group-example@googlegroups.com. 
- To refer to all members of the Google Apps for Business domain example.com, the entity would be domain-example.com.

fields.desc: The domain associated with the entity, if any.

fields.desc: The kind of item this is. For bucket access control entries, this is always storage#bucketAccessControl.

fields.name: role
fields.desc: The access permission for the entity. Can be READER, WRITER, or OWNER.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: The email address associated with the entity, if any.
